main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Galveston, Indiana on June 6, 1964, involving two objects, one stationary and the other disappearing to the south.
interesting points: The observation lasted 2-3 minutes, During the observation, one object remained stationary while the second object disappeared, The report included various conclusions, including the possibility of a balloon and an unknown origin, The sighting was conducted under a full moon which may have influenced the visibility, The report was forwarded to Gen. McConnel for further investigation.
